0. DEFINITIONS AND METRICS

"The Core" refers to the source code of the Juno compiler, its parsers, intermediate representations, analyzers, code generators, tooling, and the Juno Standard Library.

"The Runtime" refers to the compiled components of The Core, standard library functions, and initialization code that are inherently embedded into or statically/dynamically linked with the user's code to create an executable.

"The Output" refers to any data generated by executing The Core, including executable binaries, object files, Abstract Syntax Trees (AST), LSP telemetry, and diagnostics. 

"Affiliate" means any entity that directly or indirectly controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with another entity (50% or more voting rights or managerial control).

"Total Capital Inflows" means the aggregate sum of all financial resources received by an entity and its Affiliates across all jurisdictions, over a Trailing Twelve Months (TTM) period. This exhaustive definition includes: gross revenue, equity investments, debt financing, government or institutional grants, subsidies, and the initial or current market capitalization of issued cryptographic assets, utility tokens, or Initial Coin Offerings (ICOs).

"Mega-Entity" refers to any legal entity (including its Affiliates) whose Total Capital Inflows exceed $10,000,000 (Ten Million US Dollars) or equivalent.

1. CONTRACTUAL FORMATION AND MUTUAL ASSENT

This is not a "bare license." By downloading, installing, executing, or copying The Core, you establish a legally binding bilateral contract with the authors. In consideration for the valuable rights granted to you herein (which you acknowledge as sufficient consideration), you expressly agree to all limitations, waivers, and conditions specified in this Agreement.

2. EMBEDDED RUNTIME EXCEPTION AND OUTPUT RIGHTS

You retain full copyright over the original source code you write. However, executable Output generated by The Core inherently contains and relies upon The Runtime (a copyrighted derivative of The Core). 
Provided you are not a Mega-Entity, you are granted a perpetual, royalty-free license to distribute, commercialize, and retain closed-source The Runtime ONLY AS EMBEDDED within your Output. This exception immediately terminates if you breach any terms of this License. Upon termination, continued distribution of your Output constitutes copyright infringement of The Runtime embedded within it.

3. VIRAL OPEN SOURCE AND NETWORK DISTRIBUTION (COPYLEFT)

If you distribute The Core (whether modified or unmodified, in source or binary form), you must provide the Corresponding Source Code under the exact terms of this License (JHPL v2.0).
Network Loophole Closure: For the purposes of this License, providing public or internal network access to The Core (e.g., as a SaaS, Web IDE, CI/CD pipeline, or LSP backend), regardless of whether The Core is modified or unmodified, constitutes distribution and unconditionally triggers the obligation to disclose the Corresponding Source Code to all network users.

4. CONTRACTUAL WAIVER OF FAIR USE (AI & TDM)

As a bargained-for condition of this contract, you expressly waive any rights to claim "Fair Use," "Text and Data Mining exceptions" (including EU DSM Directive Article 4), or similar copyright limitations regarding the use of The Core's source code for training, tuning, or ingesting into Artificial Intelligence or Machine Learning models. Any such use without a separate commercial agreement is a material breach of contract, irrespective of copyright preemption doctrines.

5. MEGA-ENTITY M&A AND RESTRICTIONS

If you meet the definition of a Mega-Entity, the Embedded Runtime Exception (Section 2) is explicitly revoked. Mega-Entities may not use The Core to generate, execute, or distribute closed-source Output.

Change of Control (Poison Pill): If an entity that legally generated closed-source Output under Section 2 is acquired by, merges with, or transfers its intellectual property to a Mega-Entity (M&A or COTS purchase), the Embedded Runtime Exception for that specific Output is immediately revoked. The acquiring Mega-Entity must either:
a) Release the Output entirely under an OSI-approved Open Source license; or
b) Cease all distribution and execution of the Output; or
c) Obtain a commercial license from the original authors.

Anti-Circumvention: Mega-Entities may not circumvent this restriction by commissioning, financing, or directing third-party contractors, independent developers, or shell companies to generate proprietary Output on their behalf.

6. PATENT RETALIATION

By contributing code, you grant all users a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive patent license. If you or your Affiliate institute patent litigation against any party alleging that The Core infringes a patent, all rights granted to you under this License terminate immediately.

7. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY AND SEVERABILITY UNDER LOCAL LAW

THE CORE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. 
Severability (e.g., Russian Civil Code art. 401): If applicable imperative law prohibits the total exclusion of liability for intentional misconduct or harm to life/health, liability is strictly limited to the minimum extent mandated by such law. All other disclaimers remain fully enforceable.
